---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does timber paling fencing cost in Pakenham?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "In 2026, treated-pine paling fencing across Cardinia typically runs about $90–$140 per lineal metre supplied and installed, with hardwood paling a bit higher again. A standard 30-metre rear boundary at $110 per metre comes to around $3,300, before allowing for old-fence removal, a capping rail or stepped panels on a sloping block. Your written quote spells it all out." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Treated pine or hardwood — which is better here?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Treated pine is the budget-friendly choice and, properly capped and lapped, lasts well for a suburban boundary. Hardwood paling looks richer and stands up better to our high-UV summers, but costs more. Both move more than steel in the heat, so we space posts and gap palings to allow for that." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does a timber fence last in Cardinia?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A well-built, capped and treated timber fence in Pakenham conditions will generally give you 10 to 15 years or more. The enemies here are high-UV summers that fade and warp under-spec timber and clay-reactive soils that shift posts — we counter both with proper treatment, capping and concreted footings." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you match my existing timber fence?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Across older estates like Lakeside and Heritage Springs we often replace a tired run while matching the neighbour's height, paling profile and capping so the streetscape stays consistent. Shared dividing fences are covered by the Fences Act 1968, and we can supply the quote you hand to your neighbour." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Timber Paling Fencing Pakenham | Pine & Hardwood Fences | Pakenham Fencing"
  description="Timber paling fencing in Pakenham & Cardinia — treated pine & hardwood, capped & lapped, built for high-UV summers & clay soils. Free quotes — (03) 9003 0108."
  canonical="https://pakenhamfencingco.com.au/services/timber-paling-fencing/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero hero-suburb">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Timber Paling Fencing</span>
      <h1>Timber paling fencing in <span class="accent">Pakenham</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Treated-pine and hardwood paling fences &mdash; capped, lapped and built to
        last in Cardinia conditions. Warm, classic boundaries for homes right across
        Pakenham and the growth corridor.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Classic timber, built for the corridor.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 60rem;">
        <p>
          There is still nothing quite like a fresh timber paling fence for warmth
          and street appeal. Across the established estates of the Cardinia growth
          corridor &mdash; many of them early-2000s builds around Lakeside and
          Heritage Springs &mdash; the original timber boundaries are now greying,
          leaning and ready to be replaced. We rebuild them properly, matching the
          neighbours where it matters so the streetscape stays tidy.
        </p>
        <p>
          Pakenham&rsquo;s climate is hard on timber. Our high-UV summers fade and
          warp anything under-spec, and the clay-reactive soils underneath move with
          every wet and dry cycle. We answer both: posts set to the right depth in
          concrete so the run does not lean, quality capping and lapping to shed
          water and protect the paling tops, and treated pine or hardwood chosen to
          suit your budget and exposure. Done this way, a timber fence here gives you
          10 to 15 years and beyond.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Pine, hardwood and what it costs.</h3>
        <p>
          Treated-pine paling is the value option and, capped and built correctly, is
          a sound suburban boundary. Hardwood paling costs more but resists our UV
          and weather better and looks richer over time. As a 2026 guide, treated-pine
          paling runs about $90&ndash;$140 per lineal metre supplied and installed. A
          worked example: a 30-metre rear boundary at $110 per metre is roughly
          $3,300, before old-fence removal, capping upgrades or stepping for slope.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Permits, standards and shared fences.</h3>
        <p>
          Most dividing timber fences up to 2.1 metres do not need a building permit,
          but anything over 2.1 metres or a fence that also retains soil brings in
          VBA registration and the NCC rules for building near boundaries, plus any
          Cardinia Shire planning or building permit on height or corner-splay.
          Shared boundary fences are covered by the Fences Act 1968 &mdash; we supply
          the quote you hand to your neighbour &mdash; and we Dial Before You Dig
          before the post holes go in.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Related fencing &amp; areas.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 60rem;">
        <p>
          Want zero maintenance instead? Compare
          <a href="/services/colorbond-fencing/">Colorbond fencing</a>, or add a
          matching <a href="/services/gates-automation/">gate</a> to your new timber
          boundary. We install timber fencing across
          <a href="/lakeside/">Lakeside</a> and
          <a href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a> &mdash; see the full
          <a href="/cardinia-shire/">Cardinia Shire</a> area.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-lakes/">Cardinia Lakes</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/lakeside/">Lakeside</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/officer/">Officer</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Get your timber fencing quote.</h2>
        <p>Tell us your boundary length and finish and we&rsquo;ll send a clear written price.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
